You can safely approach as long as you're not lined up with him.
In an open room, you only have to be lined up when you finally
approach him.  If you have speed, you should be able to make the
final approach, and hit him with the cockatrice corpse, without
his getting a turn in between.  (Trolls are, I believe, fairly
slow.)

Of course, &quot;safely&quot; isn't perhaps the appropriate word.  When I
had that problem, it was an elf with the wand; elves are fast,
and I was a Barbarian without speed, and I ended up leaving a
bones file.  In general, it's a very delicate solution.  But it
might be worth trying, *if* you've got speed.

--
