I've always said that the RNG is actually on _our_ side -- look at all
the items and equipment it gives us throughout the game, as well as all
the random Archons it DOESN'T generate.

There's been a tag on the Spork idea page forever about &quot;nightmare
mode&quot;.  It sits there because I don't really have a good idea of how to
best implement this, but the idea is basically to show the player what
it'd look like with a _mean_ RNG... ie. any roll that would be exactly
the minimum needed to hit would miss instead, etc., etc.  The player
would enter it much like Explore mode, and it would of course be
nonreturnable.

It's a lot harder to actually implement than it is to talk about, sadly,
and probably even harder to do _properly_.  But it's a nice idea.  :)

