Being blind is indeed a condition that demands some carefulness, but as
those conditions go, it's among the easiest. It can be cured by the horn, a
spell, a food item and prayer. It is less relevant the more non-vision
means of locating monsters you have. It is even an advantage when you have
telepathy, which most characters get long before they encounter unicorns.
Plus, only one wand can blind you when engrave testing, and it belongs to
the group of wands that monsters will zap, thus it might well already be
identified.

All in all, the benefit of knowing your wands far outweigs the risk of
blinding.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; I usually engrave-test my wands asap for a lot of reasons, including BoH
&gt; accidents, permanent Elbereth, random WoW/WoDeath, effective ranged weapon.
">

